<TITLE> Regional meet backs local action for rural growth </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com)A regional conference in Dhaka called for leaving the rural development policies to the local government bodies for real development. At the conclusion of the five-day conference of the Centre on Integrated Rural Development for Asia and the Pacific (CIRDAP) Thursday, the member countries was urged to ensure access of poor people to information and communication technology for poverty alleviation. "We (the conference) emphasise the importance of empowering the local governments for effective administration of policies and progarmmes for rural development," Syed Ashraful Islam, local government minister, told reporters at a press conference at Hotel Sheraton. He read out the Dhaka Declaration adopted at the end of the conference which was attended by ministers from 14 countries of the Asia Pacific. "We further call for intensive efforts so that rural poor can get access to resources such as land, water, ICT and finance by suitable policies and programmes for rural development," said Islam, the current chair of CIRDAP. The conference took place after a pause of 23 years, first since 1987. The representatives agreed making CIRDAP a focal point in the region by sharing good experiences on rural development in the member countries, he said
